  "original_title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s presidential hopeful, withdrawn opposition leader say move was to solve crisis",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s presidential hopeful, withdrawn opposition leader say move was to solve crisis",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Presidential hopeful Dullas Alahapperuma and Opposition Leader Sajith Premadasa, who withdrew his nomination to back his rival in a surprise move, said they started a \u201ccollaborative journey\u201d to bring the country out of crisis.",
        "Premadasa, who announced his nomination last week finally proposed Alahapperuma\u2019s name in a rare coalition which analysts see as a move to defeat their common rival \u2013 Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "Addressing the public on Tuesday (19) Alahapperuma said that he was grateful for the \u201cimmense sacrifice\u201d made by Premadasa in stepping down from the Presidential race that is scheduled on Wednesday (20).",
        "\u201cHe has made a huge sacrifice,\u201d Alahapperuma said in a recorded statement while Premadasa was seating near him.",
        "Premadasa\u2019s Samagi Jana Balavegaya and the ruling party had decided to embark on a journey of unity, he said.",
        "\u201c[Sri Lanka] is in the midst of extreme economic and social crisis. Parliamentarians at times might not understand what the people want. The people were calling for a change, and the people in parliament to unite for the good of the public.",
        "\u201cIt is an act of unity that happened here, not one of greed for power.\u201d",
        "Alahapperuma said that the public must take a leaf from the Parliament\u2019s book in terms of uniting to bring the country forward and out of the ongoing crisis.",
        "\u201cNo one party or one leader can take this country out of the crisis. It is that reality that we have bowed down to.\u201d",
        "Premadasa\u2019s withdrawal has increased Alahapperuma\u2019s chances of winning the vote. However, analysts are not convinced over how all the lawmakers would use the secret ballot. Many analysts still say Wickremesinghe still has more votes to win the most unprecedented presidential poll in 29 years.",
        "In 1993, Wickremesinghe became the prime minister after then prime minister D B Wijetunga was elected by the parliament after the untimely death of President Ranasinghe Premadasa, the father of Sajith.",
        "Alahepperuma has offered the Prime Minister post if he wins Presidential vote on Wednesday.",
        "Opposition leader Sajith Premadasa said that \u201ca large majority\u201d of Parliamentarians had agreed to collaborate on the \u201cnew and creative journey\u201d to bring prosperity to the country.",
        "\u201cThis is the moment where we take the first step towards achieving prosperity for everyone regardless of [background]. We have made this sacrifice on behalf of the people,\u201d he said in the same recorded video clip.",
        "\u201cPersonal political victories must turn into victories for the country.\u201d",
        "Premadasa stated that the collaboration was an opportunity to give the constitutional reforms that people were expecting and increase participatory governance.",
        "\u201cWe are committed to safeguard the political economic social religious rights of the people. The aim of this journey to strengthen and protect the country,\u201d he said. (Colombo/July 18/2022)"
      ],
